Sharing photos with friends and family is now faster and easier than ever. After tapping share, just pick the contacts you want to share photos with – or enter any email address or phone number – and Google Photos will handle the rest.

Google Photos users will get a notification, phone numbers will get a link via SMS, and email addresses will get an email from Google Photos, saving you time and data.

No more worrying about failed texts, email attachment limits, or re-uploading the same photos every time you want to share.

Also in this update:
• Choose a new thumbnail for faces in People
• Sort photos in albums chronologically or by recently added
• Easier sharing to YouTube
• Performance improvements

Create and print photo books
• Beautiful hardcover and softcover books—perfect for every occasion.
• Make it in minutes, not hours, with automatic photo curation and easy customization.
• Made in the USA from premium, responsibly-sourced paper.

Archive photos
• Not all your photos are sunsets, selfies, or cherished memories. You probably also have photos of receipts, documents, notes, books to read, items to buy, and more.
• Move these to Archive to clean up your photo grid. Just tap the ⋯ icon after selecting photos and tap Archive.
• Archived photos remain visible in search (just search “receipts”, “documents”, etc) and albums.

More fun stuff
• Reduced amount of storage space used by the app.
• Performance improvements.

Suggested sharing
• Sharing photos with friends just got easier. Check the new Sharing tab for smart, personalized suggestions that help you quickly share the right photos with the right people.

Shared libraries
• Grant a trusted person—whether it’s a spouse, best friend, or family member—access to some, or all, of your photos. No more asking each other for photos.
• Set up rules to only share photos of specific people or time ranges.

We are changing our unlimited High quality storage policy. Starting June 1, 2021, any new photos and videos you upload in High quality will count toward your Google Account storage. All photos and videos you back up in High quality before June 1, 2021 are exempt from this change and will not count toward your Google Account storage.
